<br>
Actually, what was said was that it would be a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>high-level expansion</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. Some content it was stated would require raids, however at E3 and during many previews they very much talked up the ability to add challenging 6-person content to the game with the new scripted events system.<br>
<br>
This had people like myself very interested in PoP. I was genuinely looking forward to the expansion as something of a renaissance of the 6 person adventuring group.<br>
<br>
What did I get in exchange? The Justice trials are all I have seen of this much-touted ability to create discreet 6-person content. I miss dungeon crawling bitterly, WHERE THE HELL ARE THE DUNGEONS?!?!<br>
<br>
And now, finally <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>why in the world should advancing my character damage my enjoyment of the game</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. Sure, make 75% of the expansion unreachable, it wouldn't have phased me one iota, I haven't seen half the rest of the world anyway.<br>
<br>
But in PoP, advancement is a trap if you don't raid. Even if I god forbid manage to get into BoT and HoH, I have 4 zones to adventure in. There's no way I am getting into Tier Four planes with anything but the best guilds on the server. While there are blue areas elsewhere, the phenomenal nature of the experience rewards in there PoP zones makes them unpalatable.<br>
<br>
Nice trade! At level 60 I had a much wider variety of places to adventure. CT was while a great exp spot, not so far above the rest of the blue areas in the game that they became worthless. I could still solo quite happily in many areas of the game.<br>
<br>
I log in these days to see friends and kill time. Not sure how long I will keep that up. <p><center>
